informed choice. the new regs must be strictly enforced with regular field
testing using "secret shoppers" (ref: consumer reports) and effective
penalties for non-compliance, not limited to "internet shaming"</li>
<li>added msg should be shown as a quantity alongside sodium, sugar, etc</li>
<li>maintain a list of <i>hidden names</i> for MSG, including <i>disodium
glutayate</i> (first hand, 202008, Innovasion)</li>
